===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|-|s}}

# {{uncountable}} Things that are or can be [[know]]n about a [[topic]]
#: ''I need some more '''information''' about this issue.''
# {{uncountable}} [[data|Data]] that have been processed into a [[format]] that is understandable by its intended audience.
#: ''And as you can see in this slide, we then take the raw data and convert it into '''information'''.'' <!-- is this sense ever used by people who aren't giving PowerPoint presentations?  -->
# {{uncountable}} A service provided by [[telephone]] which provides listed telephone numbers of a subscriber: see [[411]].
# {{information theory}} Any [[unambiguous]] [[abstract]] data, the smallest possible unit being the [[bit#Etymology 3|bit]].
# {{countable|US|legal}} A sworn statement by an authorized official filed in court briefly describing the nature of each charge against a suspect, [[tantamount]] to an [[indictment]] but without the involvement of a [[grand jury]].

